===Background===
He is the Lord of [[Greywater Watch]] and the father of [[Meera Reed|Meera]] and [[Jojen Reed]]. The head of [[House Reed]], he is a loyal vassal of [[House Stark]], ruling over the bog-filled lands of [[the Neck]].Â According to [[Bran Stark]] in a conversation with Jojen Reed, Howland saved [[Eddard Stark|Ned Stark]]'s life during [[Robert's Rebellion]]. Howland apparently never told his children anything about his part in the rebellion.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Dark Wings, Dark Words]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

===[[Season 3]]===
While traveling in the [[The Gift|Gift]], Bran and Jojen talk about Howland Reed and his relation to Ned Stark. Jojen remembers that when he told his father about his visions of what had [[Execution of Eddard Stark|happened to Ned Stark]], it was the first time he saw his father cry.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Dark Wings, Dark Words]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;
